From cf6290d09196aa07905816cc99095def083039a6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hari Chandrakanthan <haric@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 28 Aug 2025 16:32:01 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd: fix tclas 10 processing and
 processing element handling

Fix the tclas 10 spi handling during nft rule creation by copying the
filter_value based on filter len.

Also include tclas processing element handling as part of rule creation.

Move nft code under CONFIG_IEEE80211AX flag as qos features are under
the same flag.

Fix the nft related code changes that exceed more than 80 characters.

Patch-dependency:
r92-01-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-CP-HOSTAPD-Register-to-receive-SCS-frame.patch
r92-02-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-HOSTAPD-Add-Robust-AV-Streaming-and-SCS-Capability.patch
r92-03-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-CP-HOSTAPD-Add-SCS-data-structs-and-sta-info-fields.patch
r92-04-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-CP-HOSTAPD-Add-support-for-SCS-req-parsing.patch
r92-06-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-CP-HOSTAPD-Handle-SCS-response-from-driver.patch

Tag: SCS
Patch-work:
https://lore.kernel.org/all/20250624205716.1052329-1-quic_rchoodam@quicinc.com/#r

Signed-off-by: Hari Chandrakanthan <haric@qti.qualcomm.com>
